\mu
X_i
E\left(\frac{X_1+X_2+X_3}{3}\right)=\frac{1}{3}\left(E(X_1)+E(X_2)+E(X_3)\right)=\mu,
E\left(\frac{X_1+2X_2+X_3}{4}\right)=\frac{1}{4}\left(E(X_1)+2E(X_2)+E(X_3)\right)=\mu.
X_i
\text{Var}\left(\frac{X_1+X_2+X_3}{3}\right)=\frac{1}{9}\left(\text{Var}(X_1)+\text{Var}(X_2)+\text{Var}(X_3)\right)=\frac{\sigma^2}{3}.
\text{Var}\left(\frac{X_1+2X_2+X_3}{4}\right)=\frac{1}{16}\left(\text{Var}(X_1)+2^2\text{Var}(X_2)+\text{Var}(X_3)\right)=\frac{6\sigma^2}{16}.
